Sentencas: AC impedance measurements were carried out under pressurized conditions by using a Ni-Y2O3-stabilized zirconia (YSZ)/YSZ half cell in order to investigate anodic polarization at high-pressure conditions.
Titulo: Characteristics of anodic polarization of solid oxide fuel cells under pressurized conditions

Sentencas: AC impedance spectra were measured at 900 and 1000 degreesC in H-2-H2O system with a constant H-2/H2O ratio, or a constant partial pressure of H-2 or H2O for different total pressures of 1 to 10 atm.
Titulo: Characteristics of anodic polarization of solid oxide fuel cells under pressurized conditions

Sentencas: At high pressures, the resistance characterized by the semicircle at high frequency was lowered, whereas that at low frequency was raised.
Titulo: Characteristics of anodic polarization of solid oxide fuel cells under pressurized conditions

Sentencas: A model based on one-dimensional diffusion was developed to estimate concentration polarization based on the impedance measurements, and activation polarization was evaluated using a linear current-potential relation derived from the Butler-Volmer equation.
Titulo: Characteristics of anodic polarization of solid oxide fuel cells under pressurized conditions

Sentencas: The activation overvoltage was at most 40 mV at 10 mA/cm(2), irrespective of the total pressure.
Titulo: Characteristics of anodic polarization of solid oxide fuel cells under pressurized conditions

Sentencas: Concentration polarization was computed to increase as the total pressure was raised, whereas it was almost constant for temperature change.
Titulo: Characteristics of anodic polarization of solid oxide fuel cells under pressurized conditions

Sentencas: Large voltage drop at small current densities was calculated for the system with low partial pressure of oxygen.
Titulo: Characteristics of anodic polarization of solid oxide fuel cells under pressurized conditions
